<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/608> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #608" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap.; cf. Liv. 7.1.8, on the death of a Censor (Postumius) in 365; Degrassi 32f., 104, 398f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/607> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #607" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Beloch (RG 83) regards this censorship as an interpolation in the Fasti, both because another censorship follows in 363 and the same gentile names appear for the Censors of 380. Münzer (RE s. v. \"Sulpicius\" 29) would accept this one but not the earlier one (see under 380). The persons named in this year can be distinguished from those in 380, and the death of one Censor is attested by Livy in 365. This would itself make another censorship necessary soon thereafter. Cram (HSC Ph 51 [1940] 78ff.) rightly defends both censorships." .
